     * [124]Parv
       buffer is the name given to the temporary memory.
       Instead of using 2*650000 bytes of memory, you can use say 1024
       bytes.
       Read from the file 1024 bytes at any instant and store it in 1024
       bytes of memory. Use this data. Then read more 1024 bytes of data
       again and so on.
       That's all what buffer is.
       Hope this helps.
       Parv
