     * [128]suitti
       2*650000 is 1,300,000 bytes. I remember when that was alot. Now
       it's a tenth of a percent of the RAM on my machine. The data would
       fit on one of those floppy drives. Computers don't even come with
       them anymore. If your compiler can't cope with this, boot your
       machine from a Knoppix CD and use that. Read and write from thumb
       drive.
       You could compile this and run it with
       myprog.exe < mybiginputfile > mybigoutputfile
       char buf[1300000];
       main( ) {
       long int i;
       if (read(1, buf, 1300000) < 0) {
       /* handle the error here */
       exit(1);
       }
       /* do whatever it is you want to do with it here, for example:
       for (i = 0; i < 1300000; i++) {
       if (i & 1) {
       buf[i] &= 0x7f;
       }
       }
       */
       if (write(2, buf, 1300000) < 0) {
       /* handle the write error here */
       exit(1);
       }
       return 0;
       }
